The paper proposes a framework for on-road localization using semantic edge features extracted from images. This involves computer vision techniques such as image retrieval and feature extraction, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The application of the framework is for vehicle localization, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques such as CASENet and VLAD also suggests that the paper may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves experimentation and analysis of results, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the use of images suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
